          "SERVICE_USER"
        ]
      },
      "date": "2012-12-17 08:30:16.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Verified\n\nTests received by maloo, run on CentOS release 6.3/x86_64: (https://maloo.whamcloud.com/test_sessions/49a8d6c8-481f-11e2-8cdc-52540035b04c).  Ran 12 tests.  No failures.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "924a2ff5a51f945b3493651bed9d8e3491b316b5",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 119,
        "name": "Alex Zhuravlev",
        "email": "bzzz@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "bzzz"
      },
      "date": "2012-12-17 16:46:07.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\n(2 inline comments)\n\nI don't see where orphan flag is set on an object - w/o this close should not initiate destroy.\n\nalso, I don't quite like the approach taken where special name is used. I'd suggest instead to use a flag.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "2abc57083184731f1ae1ac1deccc28ed89fede1e",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 140,
        "name": "jacques-Charles Lafoucriere",
        "email": "jacques-charles.lafoucriere@cea.fr",
        "username": "jcl"
      },
      "date": "2012-12-17 17:09:52.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: (2 inline comments)\n\nI agree the flag approach is better but it is difficult to add Posix flags (without a conflict risk). After discussion we choose the name approach (see JIRA spec)",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "b1201d7eba0d4f53ecddc4e3a2cf312479847008",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 119,
        "name": "Alex Zhuravlev",
        "email": "bzzz@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "bzzz"
      },
      "date": "2012-12-17 17:11:37.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nwhy does it need to be posix? i got to think llapi will be used.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "f3e02f25d00e6ff2a4f29ecf847e78b04cab7ffe",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 119,
        "name": "Alex Zhuravlev",
        "email": "bzzz@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "bzzz"
      },
      "date": "2012-12-17 17:13:23.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nplus now we're going to have unexpected behavior in case of unfortunate name collision?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "2dfe5307283ca7eb0007a4d64fa2df98291fb072",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 140,
        "name": "jacques-Charles Lafoucriere",
        "email": "jacques-charles.lafoucriere@cea.fr",
        "username": "jcl"
      },
      "date": "2012-12-18 07:10:24.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nThe need is to create a file and to get a fd to fill the file. So we have to tell throuth the open call that the file is volatile => a new posix flag or the file name. At last close the file is removed, so use of an ioctl on directory to create the file is not possible (the file will be created closed).\n\nAbout the name collision, I agree there is a risk, so it is why I use a .LSTR:.... name which has a small risk of collision (hidden file + LST header).",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "48cf4d2d357fb4b01606d9426a58055f13681f8e",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 7,
        "name": "Johann Lombardi",
        "email": "johann.lombardi@intel.com",
        "username": "johann",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2012-12-18 07:47:38.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> why does it need to be posix? i got to think llapi will be used.\n\nWe will definitely provide llapi wrappers, but at the end of the day, we need to do a syscall that returns a file descriptor for the open/unlinked file, that's why we overload open by using a special name. Another option would be to use an  open flag (like O_LOV_DELAY_CREATE), but such a flag is more likely to collide (we have already had problems with O_LOV_DELAY_CREATE) than using a binary name.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "35b291601218d9142be98ff1d0582e0ec5a0a60d",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 140,
        "name": "jacques-Charles Lafoucriere",
        "email": "jacques-charles.lafoucriere@cea.fr",
        "username": "jcl"
      },
      "date": "2012-12-18 12:17:21.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nforget this patch, I am working on a new design based on use of orphan method (no more need of mdd_orphans type change)",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
